usdAtmAgent.name: usdAtmAgent

revisions.description: Added ATM switched virtual connection (SVC) support to the Unisphere-Data-ATM-MIB VCC end point capabilities.
Added support for ATM connection admission control (CAC) to the Unisphere-Data-ATM-MIB VCC end point capabilities.
The initial release of this management information module.

usdAtmAgent.contactinfo: Unisphere Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@UnisphereNetworks.com
usdAtmAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the ATM component of the SNMP agent in the Unisphere Routing Switch family of products.

usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV1.name: usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV1
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the ATM VCC end point agent subcomponent of the Unisphere
        Routing Switch SNMP agent.  This version of the ATM end point
        subcomponent was supported in the Unisphere RX 3.0 and 3.1 system
        releases.
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV1.description: The MIBs supported by the SNMP agent for the ATM application in the Unisphere Routing Switch. These capabilities became obsolete when new objects were added to the usdAtmSubIfGroup and support for the atmfM4IfLoopbackLocationCode object was added.

usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV2.name: usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV2
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV2.productrelease:
Version 2 of the ATM VCC end point agent subcomponent of the Unisphere
        Routing Switch SNMP agent.  This version of the ATM end point
        subcomponent was supported in the Unisphere RX 3.2 and RX 3.3 system
        releases.
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV2.description: The MIBs supported by the SNMP agent for the ATM application in the Unisphere Routing Switch. These capabilities became obsolete when support was added to the Unisphere-Data-ATM-MIB for connection admission control (CAC).

usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV3.name: usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV3
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV3.productrelease:
Version 3 of the ATM VCC end point agent subcomponent of the Unisphere
        Routing Switch SNMP agent.  This version of the ATM end point
        subcomponent was supported in the Unisphere RX 3.4 and subsequent 3.x
        system releases.
usdAtmVccEndPointAgentV3.description: The MIBs supported by the SNMP agent for the ATM application in the Unisphere Routing Switch. These capabilities became obsolete when support was added to the Unisphere-Data-ATM-MIB for switched virtual connection (SVC).
